webpackJsonp([0x896564d11584],{346:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p><a href="https://github.com/AntCas/OpenPanoThermo">https://github.com/AntCas/OpenPanoThermo</a></p>\n<p>Project thermo reliably creates thermographic panoramas of indoor locations in order to identify energy inefficiencies in rooms and buildings.</p>\n<p>I worked on this project as a volunteer at the Human Computer Interaction lab at the University of Maryland, College Park during my last semester there as a Computer Science senior.</p>\n<p>The software I wrote was integrated into a self-contained device which could take a series of thermographic images over the course of several days in order to map heat issues over time.</p>\n<p>The project is a fork of <a href="https://github.com/ppwwyyxx/OpenPano">OpenPano</a> adapted for thermographic images.</p>\n<p>After many dead-ends I ended up achieving great results by first normalizing and enhancing the images using (ImageMagick)[https://www.imagemagick.org/script/index.php], then stitching them together using OpenPano.</p>\n<p>[Images]</p>',frontmatter:{date:"January 01, 2017",path:"/hcil",title:"HCIL - Project Thermo"}}},pathContext:{}}}});
